Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.82,0:00:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without the first issue,\Nwe're not getting anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.11,0:00:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.53,0:00:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't hurt to bring\NSatoshi and Ibara in on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.19,0:00:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, um, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.49,0:00:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, even supposing we\Nnever solve this mystery,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.94,0:00:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,someday, your own statute\Nof limitations might expire.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.49,0:00:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Statute of limitations?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.99,0:00:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.44,0:00:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will ask Fukube-{\i1}san {\i0}and\NMayaka-{\i1}san{\i0}, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.69,0:00:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.61,0:00:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about what happened\Nto my uncle, 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.78,0:00:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, I'm asking for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.57,0:00:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your uncle, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.86,0:00:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That really happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.78,0:01:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The untold story of a heroic tale,\Nuncovered by someone 45 years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.36,0:01:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were just checking out\Nsome things from that time period.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.74,0:01:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. This picture\Nis intriguing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.36,0:01:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's some reason for it,\NI'd like to know, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.04,0:01:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is kind of getting exciting, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.74,0:01:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If things work out right, this could\Nbe material for our anthology.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.90,0:01:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can investigate all we want,\Nand call it a Classic Lit Club activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.49,0:01:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, looking into\Nthe Classic Lit Club's past
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.07,0:01:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had become the top priority\Nfor all of its members.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.90,0:01:35.32,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I scowled at the wind blowing\Nat my window of boredom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.32,0:01:43.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I could turn away\Nthe awkwardness I was feeling{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.65,0:01:51.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.54,0:01:56.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I nod noncommittally at today\Nas I hold it in my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.96,0:02:02.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}projecting myself a little exaggeratedly{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.34,0:02:07.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get the feeling that\Nsomething is about to change{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.86,0:02:12.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's all because of you\Ncalling out to my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.36,0:02:19.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Peeking up at cloudy skies,\NI sense what's coming{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.78,0:02:27.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's reach out our hands\Nwith courage stronger than ever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.20,0:02:32.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light and shadow are both still far off{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.78,0:02:39.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but even so, we want to know\Nthe reason for this kindness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.05,0:02:46.47,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go look now, beyond the brilliance\Nthat goes by nobody's name{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.47,0:02:59.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}before it all becomes a thing of the past{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.61,0:03:04.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Classic Lit Club's\NGlorious Days of Yore
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.95,0:03:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! Been waiting long?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.65,0:03:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you, Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.15,0:03:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pipe down! Have you no sense of shame?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.78,0:03:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, got all your material ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.53,0:03:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about {\i1}you{\i0}, Hotaro?\NFind anything good?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.86,0:03:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we can look forward\Nto your hypothesis, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.28,0:03:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, crap. Were we supposed to do that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.65,0:03:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.63,0:03:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being such wealthy farmers,\Nthe Chitanda family mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.43,0:03:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ranks in the top class of all of Kamiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.07,0:03:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure enjoying yourself, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.24,0:03:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because I love cycling.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.65,0:03:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Slicing through the wind under\Nthe power of your own legs like this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.57,0:04:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that, I mean your\Nentire high school life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.69,0:04:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the whole "rosy" business, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.74,0:04:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My basic attitude is to be rosy,\Nno matter what's going on around me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.52,0:04:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More like shocking pink, don't you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.03,0:04:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great! If we're going with that,\Nthen you'd be gray, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.40,0:04:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you said before, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.40,0:04:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did? Still, I'm not trying to\Ndiminish you by saying that, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.99,0:04:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.03,0:04:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My basic attitude is\Nshocking pink, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.19,0:04:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it won't work if someone\Ntries to color me rosy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.19,0:04:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't accept the color.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.07,0:04:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you already unusually tinged?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:38.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.24,0:04:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Hotaro? Do you say that because\NI'm busy with the executive committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.69,0:04:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Handicrafts Club, and Classic Lit Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.82,0:04:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.07,0:04:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you are. Whatever I choose\Nto do, I still am who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.15,0:04:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't mean I'm "tinged."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.82,0:04:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm trying to diminish you,\NI'll say you have {\i1}no {\i0}color.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.61,0:04:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.19,0:05:01.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not looking to endear myself to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.69,0:05:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.44,0:05:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Hotaro, how did you\Ndo on your midterm tests?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.32,0:05:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Average marks on all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.11,0:05:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our gray Hotaro for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.36,0:05:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.03,0:05:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming into view now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.65,0:05:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Chitanda estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.78,0:05:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something else, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.99,0:05:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go. Chitanda and Ibara are waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.53,0:05:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, okay. Hotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.53,0:05:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like a servant might\Ngreet us, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.99,0:05:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome! I've been expecting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.61,0:05:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.07,0:05:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon the intrusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.90,0:05:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on in. This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.49,0:06:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please sit anywhere you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.86,0:06:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure took your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.28,0:06:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.69,0:06:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.94,0:06:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's rare to see a man so unsuited\Nto sit at the head of the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.32,0:06:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, shall we get this\Nreview meeting started?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.77,0:06:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.78,0:06:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.27,0:06:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.44,0:06:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, I would like to consider\Nthe incident that happened
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.32,0:06:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the Classic Lit Club 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.03,0:06:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we do get to the bottom of anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.99,0:06:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to include it\Nin this year's anthology.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.24,0:06:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we'll share and report on our data,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.90,0:06:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then we'll all ask our questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.87,0:06:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then comes the presenter's hypothesis,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.99,0:06:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and finally, discussion of that hypothesis,\Nand that's how we'll proceed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.54,0:06:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ho, she's quite the\Naccomplished meeting leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.15,0:06:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, for the first report... Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.28,0:06:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, who should we have go first?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.94,0:06:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then again...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.68,0:06:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter, does it?\NChitanda, {\i1}you {\i0}go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.01,0:07:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then, I'll start,\Nand we'll proceed clockwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.90,0:07:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The subject of my research\Nwas {\i1}Hyouka {\i0}itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.27,0:07:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing that touched on\Nwhat happened 45 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was this foreword. I compiled\Nthe facts that I gathered from it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.45,0:07:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and listed them on the second page.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.28,0:07:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, Item 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.82,0:07:21.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,1. 'Senpai' has departed (from where?)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.94,0:07:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Senpai" refers to my uncle, Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.78,0:07:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle dropped out of\NKamiyama High School,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.90,0:07:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and his academic career ends\Nas a middle-school graduate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.78,0:07:30.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,2. 'Senpai' was a hero 45 years ago,\Nand a legend 44 year ago
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.78,0:07:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next is Item 2, but I think that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it shows that as time passes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.36,0:07:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the story becomes more exaggerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.63,0:07:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Items 3 and 5 are connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.63,0:07:44.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,3. 'Senpai' was a 'quiet warrior' and a 'kind hero.'\N5. The conflict\Nhad a casualty (casualty = 'Senpai'?)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.32,0:07:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The quiet, kind "Senpai,"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.24,0:07:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after turning warrior, became a hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.07,0:07:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and finally... a sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.77,0:07:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,4. 'Senpai' gave {\i1}Hyouka {\i0}its name
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.57,0:07:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Item 4 is a curious matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.53,0:07:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but let's leave that aside for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.53,0:07:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is my presentation.\NAre there any questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.70,0:07:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us, why did you exclude where it says
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.70,0:08:00.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,heroic tale
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.07,0:08:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It was in no way a heroic tale"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.86,0:08:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because that was the\Nwriter's own mental image.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.57,0:08:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could mean that the fighting was\Ndown-and-dirty, not something awe-inspiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.53,0:08:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.99,0:08:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll present my hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:14.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,What
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.78,0:08:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's conceivable that my uncle\Nwas contending against something,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.65,0:08:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and as a result, he left the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.22,0:08:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's one other factor,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.03,0:08:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,besides the other five that\NI gave, that I thought of.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.74,0:08:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This part here about it\Nhaving been "a year since."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.57,0:08:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means that it was around the time\Nof the Kanyasai that my uncle left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.32,0:08:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I may digress a little, I heard\Nfrom a friend at another high school
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that there was an incident\Nat the culture festival last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.15,0:08:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A culture festival shakedown, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.67,0:08:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sellers getting extorted, and their\Nproceeds disappearing, or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.69,0:08:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that there are\Nso-called punks in any age.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.11,0:08:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if the Kanyasai that year was
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.78,0:08:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,unlucky enough to be\Ntargeted by such folks,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.29,0:08:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and so my uncle fought back\Nagainst them violently,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.46,0:08:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which is what made him a hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.74,0:08:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the underclassmen who hated to see my\Nuncle have to leave school to answer for doing so
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.32,0:09:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wrote this piece as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.19,0:09:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.97,0:09:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.85,0:09:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.78,0:09:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No good? Please tell me why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.69,0:09:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, when you first\Nbrought up the anthology,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.19,0:09:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do you remember what\NI said to counter the idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.99,0:09:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...\NA refreshment stand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.57,0:09:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. But you said that refreshment\Nstands were traditionally prohibited.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.82,0:09:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody would come rip off a Kanyasai\Nwhere no money changes hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.15,0:09:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that some might come to it,\Neven if money wasn't involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.19,0:09:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pathetic, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.25,0:09:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Then let's all hear\Nwhat you think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.15,0:09:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Punks hassling the culture festival\N45 years ago would,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.65,0:09:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,marvel of marvels, never have\Nhappened in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.69,0:09:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.90,0:09:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you think of the 1960s,\Ndoesn't it bring to mind something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.86,0:09:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.99,0:09:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo? The Diet Building?\NPlacards? Demonstrations?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.56,0:09:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, what are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.44,0:09:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Student activism.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.32,0:10:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember, the sort of campus violence\Nthat Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}speaks of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.94,0:10:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was yet to be seen during the 1960s.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.36,0:10:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was an era when we weren't\Nfighting teachers or schools;
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.16,0:10:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,instead it was the state, and the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.83,0:10:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say it like you were there to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.19,0:10:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, I checked\Nthis time period out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.19,0:10:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, I overlooked any\Nsense of the era it was in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.69,0:10:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's come over you all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.82,0:10:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The material I have doesn't\Nfit in with your explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.74,0:10:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn next, so I wasn't\Nsure how much I should say here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.94,0:10:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, Ibara! Why didn't you\Nstop me from wasting my breath?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.81,0:10:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, we'll withdraw\Nmy theory for the time being,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.40,0:10:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so Mayaka-{\i1}san{\i0}, please tell us\Nwhat your explanation is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right with everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.40,0:10:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.\NYes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.95,0:10:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, my legs are falling asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.36,0:10:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to say, this mansion is huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.03,0:10:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a pond out\Nin your gardens, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.74,0:10:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.32,0:10:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! I'd sure like to see that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.82,0:10:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I want to see it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.13,0:11:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, why don't we continue\Nin a different location?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.32,0:11:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is very comfortable out on the veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.15,0:11:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pond, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.01,0:11:10.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Boushu {\i0}('The Seeding')\NThe time to sow bearded grains
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.36,0:11:10.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.19,0:11:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a copy of the book\N{\i1}Solidarity and Salutes, Issue 1{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.69,0:11:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which I found in the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't find issues 2 and higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.65,0:11:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was published 45 years\Nago, just like Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.33,0:11:30.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Solidarity and Salutes, Issue 1
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.99,0:11:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Our valiant activism," is it?\NSounds so old-fashioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.90,0:11:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll start, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.15,0:11:39.29,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,We
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.15,0:11:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, "we" refers to the students,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.29,0:11:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while "reactionary forces" and "authoritarians"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.29,0:11:43.67,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Reactionary forces\NAuthoritarians
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.42,0:11:43.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,refer to the teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.68,0:11:45.93,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,June
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.68,0:11:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a conflict\Nduring June of the previous year,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.93,0:11:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and its leader was Sekitani Jun,\Npresident of the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.30,0:11:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They engaged in what they called activism,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.30,0:11:54.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Activism
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.28,0:11:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,sticking it to the teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.19,0:11:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the reading of this word\Nmeans "conflict," does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.74,0:12:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This{\i1} Solidarity and Salutes\N{\i0}seems a little hinky somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.78,0:12:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hinky?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.19,0:12:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that I'm questioning this account.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.82,0:12:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking that someone\Nwho was caught up in college
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.99,0:12:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or other illustrious movements wrote this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.07,0:12:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, does that have any bearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.15,0:12:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm just thinking out loud.\NSorry, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.83,0:12:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, are there any other questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.82,0:12:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, here's my hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.69,0:12:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, I reject Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}'s theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.28,0:12:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to {\i1}Solidarity and Salutes{\i0},\Nthe incident happened in June.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.65,0:12:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the "action" that led\Nto him having to leave school,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.15,0:12:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,violence is what comes to mind, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.07,0:12:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the people who were led by\NSekitani Jun let the teachers have some of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.32,0:12:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and gave them what for.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.24,0:12:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure if he actually\Nhit anyone, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.11,0:12:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But something happened to deprive the\Nstudents of their autonomy 45 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.53,0:12:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they must have been\Nrallying against that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.65,0:12:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle did?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.41,0:12:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.15,0:12:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I kind of understand what\Nyou're getting at, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.07,0:12:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.36,0:13:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka, your theory is that\Nthe students resorted to violence
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.99,0:13:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to resist the oppression\Nof the teachers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.57,0:13:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your theory is too abstract.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.44,0:13:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we also can't interpret\Nanything more from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.11,0:13:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, if you're talking about specifics,\NI might not have any,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.07,0:13:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but are there any inconsistencies?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.31,0:13:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.06,0:13:20.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka\NSolidarity and Salutes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.06,0:13:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you believe\Nboth {\i1}Hyouka{\i0} and {\i1}Solidarity and Salutes{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.03,0:13:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the incident occurred in June,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.03,0:13:23.82,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,April\NOctober
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.24,0:13:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he left school in October,\Nwhen the culture festival takes place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he\Nwas being punished for acts of violence,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:28.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Apr. May June July Aug. Sept. Oct.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he would have\Nbeen expelled right after the incident, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.90,0:13:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.99,0:13:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This four-month differential\Nalso has me curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.32,0:13:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says it had already been\Na year since the culture festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.15,0:13:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'm thinking he left school in October.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.79,0:13:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, you're all so nitpicky.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.74,0:13:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you're heading in\Nthe right direction, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.07,0:13:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.24,0:13:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, is it okay if I end my turn now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.28,0:13:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Thank you very much. Okay, next...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.17,0:13:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I guess I'm getting hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.40,0:13:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, you ate all those snacks, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.11,0:13:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.53,0:13:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can make you some {\i1}onigiri{\i0},\Nif you'd like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.64,0:14:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about the rest of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.24,0:14:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, anything I can do to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.61,0:14:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.12,0:14:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.16,0:14:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.82,0:14:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Handmade!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.03,0:14:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure seem pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.82,0:14:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}, isn't this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.92,0:14:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.15,0:14:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to my data,\Nyour theory is partially negated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.03,0:14:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.49,0:14:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.74,0:14:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm? Is this the Kami High\NMonthly Newsletter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Togaito did say\Nthey were nearing their 500th issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.44,0:14:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.90,0:14:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I checked into were\Nthe back-number issues
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.10,0:14:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the Wall Newspaper Club's\N"Kami High Monthly Newsletter."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.57,0:15:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About the only thing that mentions\Nany incident 45 years ago was this article.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.62,0:15:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I put a summary on the second page.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.91,0:15:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first one and the last one are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.91,0:15:08.04,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,No violence occurred during the incident.\NNonviolent resistance was\Nmaintained during the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.86,0:15:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no incidents\Nof violence during the incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.53,0:15:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so Mayaka, your theory is off-course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.13,0:15:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, if the whole school, or all of its students,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.13,0:15:14.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The incident affected the whole school.\NDuring the incident, 'we'\Nwere in solidarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.07,0:15:14.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Whole school = We
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.07,0:15:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the same as "we,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.43,0:15:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would mean that the incident\Ninvolved all of the students;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.49,0:15:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if not, it would mean that someone who had won\Nthe support of the all the students was involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.15,0:15:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.40,0:15:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.36,0:15:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.78,0:15:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.32,0:15:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are plum, kelp,\Nand mustard leaf varieties.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.90,0:15:32.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, help yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.74,0:15:35.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for these.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.90,0:15:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm? What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.62,0:15:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.74,0:15:43.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.82,0:15:44.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.69,0:15:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.36,0:15:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, did your\Nfamily grow this rice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.11,0:15:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.36,0:15:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, if you have any questions, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.03,0:15:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you positive that this\N"legendary movement"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.32,0:15:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is the incident that forced\NSekitani Jun to leave school?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.90,0:15:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems awfully thin\Ngoing by just this copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.24,0:16:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows? There's no proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.07,0:16:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows? Then it doesn't\Ncount as data, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.61,0:16:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, maybe not, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.07,0:16:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, there is some indirect evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.48,0:16:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the "Sekitani Jun Incident"and the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.48,0:16:16.49,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Sekitani Jun Incident
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.69,0:16:16.49,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Legendary Movement
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.90,0:16:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are different,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.11,0:16:16.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there would be something\Nthat said that of the two,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}this one {\i0}is the legendary movement,\Nwouldn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah! That's what I was trying\Nto say! Leave it to you, Mayaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.15,0:16:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.49,0:16:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, your hypothesis, if you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.69,0:16:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, my hypothesis?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.61,0:16:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.03,0:16:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, I hate to say it,\Nbut I can't offer a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.19,0:16:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all I can do to correct the\NIbara theory with what little I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.88,0:16:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, databases don't draw conclusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.97,0:16:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew he would say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.01,0:16:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.94,0:16:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\NNot at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.78,0:16:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, if you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.86,0:16:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, this wouldn't happen to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.90,0:16:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kamiyama High School's 50-Year Progress"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.07,0:17:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought there might be something\Nwritten in the public record.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.08,0:17:07.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Showa 42 (1967)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.08,0:17:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, looking at it again now,\Nthere's nothing worth mentioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.91,0:17:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no hypothesis, either.\NWhat should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.28,0:17:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something the matter, Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.69,0:17:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, have you forgotten how\Nyou're supposed to proceed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.07,0:17:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You start with your summary.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.94,0:17:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this even something\NI {\i1}have {\i0}to do to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.36,0:17:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.11,0:17:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.36,0:17:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.11,0:17:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should I blow this off?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.44,0:17:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.94,0:17:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot I had shiitake\Nmushrooms drying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.36,0:17:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to hurry and bring them in!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.28,0:17:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you handle it alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.74,0:17:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.44,0:17:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.44,0:17:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.79,0:17:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but can I use your restroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.94,0:17:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. Go out this door,\Nand then head straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.78,0:18:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Getting nervous, or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.99,0:18:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Straight... Straight...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.03,0:18:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.36,0:18:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She researched it this much?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.61,0:18:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I can put my brain\Nto work for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.53,0:18:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,45 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.44,0:18:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An event that happened to Sekitani Jun...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.69,0:18:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Four different references...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.82,0:18:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it that ties them together?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.57,0:18:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.64,0:18:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Student activism... Acts of violence...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.86,0:18:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time interval before expulsion...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.24,0:19:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,45 years ago, Sekitani Jun was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.15,0:19:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were in there quite a while, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.99,0:19:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, excuse me. It was\Nmy turn to present, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.28,0:19:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, but I didn't\Nprepare a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.69,0:19:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So could we end my turn,\Nand move right to the wrap-up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.57,0:19:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, you came up with something, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.99,0:19:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, maybe. It should provide\Na general explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.15,0:19:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've figured something out,\Nhaven't you, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.26,0:19:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.28,0:19:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hear it, then.\NDon't disappoint us, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.61,0:19:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I'll explain this by steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.35,0:19:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First is the "when." 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.11,0:19:41.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,45 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.65,0:19:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time period is the issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.03,0:19:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we believe both {\i1}Hyouka\N{\i0}and {\i1}Solidarity and Salutes{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.24,0:19:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the incident happened in June,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.24,0:19:47.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Incident... June
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.61,0:19:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the {\i1}senpai {\i0}left in October.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.69,0:19:48.62,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Expulsion... October
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.37,0:19:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next is the "where."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.36,0:19:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was at Kamiyama High School.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.36,0:19:54.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiyama High School
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.40,0:19:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the "who,"\Naccording to {\i1}Solidarity and Salutes{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.49,0:20:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the primary figure in the incident was\NClassic Lit Club President Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.15,0:20:00.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekitani Jun
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.50,0:20:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the "Kami High Monthly Newsletter,"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.30,0:20:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we know that the entire\Nstudent body was involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.51,0:20:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the "why." The ones that all\Nthe students were rising up against
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.19,0:20:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would have to be the teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.99,0:20:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To borrow Ibara's words,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.69,0:20:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the reason why they rose up is that\Nthey were deprived of their autonomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.65,0:20:16.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Deprived of autonomy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.28,0:20:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the cause of the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.69,0:20:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was the culture festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.07,0:20:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did it say somewhere that the culture\Nfestival was the cause of the incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.15,0:20:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but as I see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.62,0:20:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,June
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.15,0:20:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in June, the students\Nand the teachers discussed it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.36,0:20:37.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,October
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.36,0:20:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they decided that the\Nculture festival would be held in October.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.03,0:20:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By "discuss,"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.08,0:20:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do you mean this "meeting to\Nconsider the culture festival" part?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.25,0:20:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Take a close look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.78,0:20:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are circle and square\Nmarks at the top of each entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.49,0:20:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it! The squares are\Ncustomary events held every year,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.53,0:20:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while the circles are things\Nthat only happened that year!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.65,0:21:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I looked at the other years, too,\Nand that much is unmistakable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.74,0:21:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why was there a meeting that was only held 45\Nyears ago to consider the culture festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.99,0:21:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because of strong\Ndemand from the students.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.24,0:21:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hints to that here in {\i1}Hyouka{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.82,0:21:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.11,0:21:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"In this last year, he has gone\Nfrom being a hero to a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.36,0:21:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culture festival will have another\Nrousing five-day run this year."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.40,0:21:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the point isn't\Nthat it will have a "run,"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.13,0:21:23.67,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,five-day
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.13,0:21:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but that it will be a "five-day" run.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.67,0:21:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.92,0:21:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "five-day" part is the achievement\Nthat the hero, Sekitani Jun, won.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.82,0:21:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just a guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.28,0:21:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but taken with the principal declaring\Nan emphasis on academic aptitude here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.39,0:21:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if the\Nprincipal wasn't trying to shorten
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.39,0:21:39.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Five days
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.19,0:21:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the usual five-day culture festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.69,0:21:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably why the whole\Nschool was in such a fiery rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.32,0:21:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the cause of the\Nincident... the "why."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.61,0:21:50.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the actual act, the "how"...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.86,0:21:52.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Classic Lit Club President Sekitani Jun
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.86,0:21:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "valiant activism" supported by
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.90,0:21:54.74,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Heroic leadership
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.90,0:21:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"heroic leadership" was carried out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.74,0:21:57.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Valiant activism
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.74,0:22:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This leads to the final "what."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.24,0:22:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The students did not engage in violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.65,0:22:02.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Violence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.57,0:22:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, it rose to\Nthe level of boycotting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.54,0:22:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The school had no choice but\Nto discuss it with the students,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.67,0:22:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and abandoned shortening\Nthe culture festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.18,0:22:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the toll for that was the\Nexpulsion of the hero, Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.55,0:22:18.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Incident: June\NExpulsion: October
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.55,0:22:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why was there so much time between\Nthe incident and his expulsion?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.78,0:22:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they had expelled Sekitani Jun,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.57,0:22:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the furor would have gotten even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.31,0:22:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As such, they probably waited\Nuntil after the culture festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.69,0:22:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when all the hoopla had died down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.95,0:22:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all for my wrap-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.82,0:22:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,45 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.57,0:22:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's what happened to my uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.99,0:22:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive work, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.69,0:22:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that was pretty nicely done,\NHotaro. Mm-hm, it makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.74,0:22:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not Oreki again! I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.61,0:22:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just stumbled into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.94,0:23:01.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does anyone have any questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.49,0:23:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No objections.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.65,0:23:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to say it, but I think he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.94,0:23:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm. Well then,\Nlet's center this year's anthology
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.57,0:23:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,around Oreki's theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.36,0:23:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll consider the content\Nin more detail at a later date.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.03,0:23:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's now adjourn the meeting.\NThank you, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.15,0:23:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.94,0:23:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.15,0:23:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was all because of you, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.28,0:23:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to have to borrow\Nan umbrella. Well, bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.94,0:23:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.15,0:23:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if that were true, why did I start crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.90,0:24:04.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:08.71,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.71,0:24:12.71,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.71,0:24:17.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.19,0:24:38.15,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heat of your budding warmth troubles me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.03,0:24:48.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't you understand how I feel yet?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.46,0:24:55.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There isn't supposed to be\Nany significance in your glance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.96,0:25:01.24,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean, it's the same one\Nyou give all your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.24,0:25:07.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The tiny wishing star fading\Ninto the morning light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.06,0:25:11.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the magic it works during the night\N(I wish you would notice){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.94,0:25:15.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.11,0:25:18.82,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.82,0:25:22.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.69,0:25:27.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.11,0:25:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "The Truth About the\NHistoric Classic Lit Club."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.36,0:25:41.60,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Truth About the Historic Classic Lit Club
